        <h1>Outreach of Mountain Forum Himalayas</h1>
        <p>
            Mountain Forum Himalayas (MFH) is a pioneering organization working to enhance the quality of life and sustainability in the remote 
            and fragile Himalayan regions of Himachal Pradesh and Uttarakhand. With a focus on disaster risk reduction, climate resilience, 
            and sustainable livelihoods, MFH empowers local communities to thrive amidst environmental and socio-economic challenges.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
            MFH is committed to fostering sustainable mountain development by addressing critical issues such as climate change, ecological 
            degradation, and socio-economic vulnerabilities. By promoting participatory development and leveraging local knowledge, MFH creates 
            impactful solutions tailored to the unique needs of Himalayan communities.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Approach</h2>
        <p><strong>Regional Focus</strong></p>
        <p>
            Himachal Pradesh: MFH operates extensively in tribal districts like Lahaul-Spiti, Kinnaur, Pangi, and Bharmour, addressing climate change 
            impacts, disaster preparedness, and sustainable agriculture.
            <br>
            Uttarakhand: In the disaster-prone districts of Kumaon and Garhwal, MFH works on climate adaptation, biodiversity conservation, and 
            resilient livelihoods.
        </p>

